  print prompt
  gets.chomp
end

def calculate_tax(income, rate)
  income * rate / 100
end

def main
  income = get_input("Enter your income: ").to_f
  rate = get_input("Enter the tax rate (percentage): ").to_f

  net_income = income - tax

  puts "Tax rate: #{rate}%"
  puts "Tax: #{tax}"
  puts "Net income: #{net_income}"
end

# Set up Piet program
program = "
:white
:stack
  'dlrow olleH'   # Push 'Hello world' onto stack
  !strdup         # Duplicate string
  # Reverse the string
  |continue       # Jump here after reversing
  @get1           # Pop next character
  ?no             # Jump to 'yes' or 'no' depending on value
  /rev            # Reverse the stack
  :yes
  !putchar        # Output character
  ->             # Jump to start of loop
"

# Compile program into an image
img = Piet.compile(program, output_filename: 'hello_world.png')

# Save the image
File.open('hello_world.png', 'wb') do |file|
  file.write(img.to_blob)
end

require 'chunky_png'

def colors_matrix_to_image(matrix, file_name)
  height = matrix.length
  width = matrix[0].length
  image = ChunkyPNG::Image.new(width, height)

  matrix.each_with_index do |row, y|
    row.each_with_index do |color, x|
      image[x, y] = ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(color[0], color[1], color[2])
    end
  end

  image.save(file_name)
end

# 定义简化版 Piet 编译器类
class SimplePietCompiler
  def initialize(source_code)
    @source_code = source_code
  end

  def compile
    if @source_code.strip == 'puts "hello"'
      simple_hello_world_piet_program
    else
      raise "Unsupported source code."
    end
  end

  private

  # 提供一个非常简化的hello world Piet程序
  def simple_hello_world_piet_program
    [
      [1,2,1,1,1],
      [0,2,2,2,0]
    ]
  end
end

# 根据简化版 Piet 编译器创建图像
class PietImageBuilder
  DEFAULT_COLORS = [
    ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(255, 192, 192),
    ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(255, 255, 192)
  ]

  def build_image(piet_program)
    height = piet_program.size
    width = piet_program[0].size

    image = ChunkyPNG::Image.new(width, height, ChunkyPNG::Color::WHITE)
    piet_program.each_with_index do |row, y|
      row.each_with_index do |cell, x|
        image[x, y] = DEFAULT_COLORS[cell] if cell > 0
      end
    end
    image
  end
end

require 'chunky_png'

def create_piet_image_from_string(input_string, output_image_path)
  width = input_string.length
  height = 2
  codel_size = 10

  # 根据字符串长度创建一张宽度为字符串长度、高度为2的图片
  image = ChunkyPNG::Image.new(width * codel_size, height * codel_size, ChunkyPNG::Color::WHITE)

  input_string.each_char.with_index do |char, index|
    color_index = char.ord % 6

    # 根据字符 ASCII 编码设置一个颜色值
    color = case color_index
            when 0 then ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(192, 0, 0)       # 红色
            when 1 then ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(0, 192, 0)       # 绿色
            when 2 then ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(0, 0, 192)       # 蓝色
            when 3 then ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(192, 192, 0)     # 黄色
            when 4 then ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(192, 0, 192)     # 品红
            when 5 then ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(0, 192, 192)     # 青色
            end

    # 将颜色值填充到图像中
    image.rect(index * codel_size, 0, (index + 1) * codel_size - 1, codel_size - 1, color, color)
  end

  # 保存生成的 Piet 图像到输出路径
  image.save(output_image_path)
end

require 'chunky_png'

class Color
  attr_accessor :color_table

  def initialize(color_table = nil)
    @color_table = color_table || [1, 0]
  end

  def rgb
    case @color_table[1]
    when 0
      # Red
      return [255, 192, 192] if @color_table[0] == 0
      return [255, 0, 0] if @color_table[0] == 1
      return [192, 0, 0] if @color_table[0] == 2
    when 1
      # Yellow
      return [255, 255, 192] if @color_table[0] == 0
      return [255, 255, 0] if @color_table[0] == 1
      return [192, 192, 0] if @color_table[0] == 2
    when 2
      # Green
      return [192, 255, 192] if @color_table[0] == 0
      return [0, 255, 0] if @color_table[0] == 1
      return [0, 192, 0] if @color_table[0] == 2
    when 3
      # Cyan
      return [192, 255, 255] if @color_table[0] == 0
      return [0, 255, 255] if @color_table[0] == 1
      return [0, 192, 192] if @color_table[0] == 2
    when 4
      # Blue
      return [192, 192, 255] if @color_table[0] == 0
      return [0, 0, 255] if @color_table[0] == 1
      return [0, 0, 192] if @color_table[0] == 2
    when 5
      # Magenta
      return [255, 192, 255] if @color_table[0] == 0
      return [255, 0, 255] if @color_table[0] == 1
      return [192, 0, 192] if @color_table[0] == 2
    end
  end

  def push_color
    @color_table[0] = (@color_table[0] + 1) % 3
    rgb
  end

  def write_color
    @color_table[0] = (@color_table[0] + 2) % 3
    @color_table[1] = (@color_table[1] + 5) % 6
    rgb
  end
end

piet_painting = ChunkyPNG::Image.new(12, 12, ChunkyPNG::Color::WHITE)

def draw_block(size, num)
  block = ChunkyPNG::Image.new(12, 12, ChunkyPNG::Color::WHITE)

  if num > 0
    old_push_color = current_color.push_color
    current_color.write_color
    block[0, 0] = ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(*old_push_color)

    size += 1
  else
    block[0, 0] = ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(*current_color.rgb)
  end

  pix_lft = 144 - size
  div = pix_lft / 12
  rem = pix_lft % 12

  if div != 0
    (0..11).each do |i|
      (12 - div...12).each do |j|
        block[i, j] = ChunkyPNG::Color::BLACK
      end
    end
  end

  (0..11 - div).each do |i|
    (0...rem).each do |j|
      block[i, j] = ChunkyPNG::Color::BLACK
    end
  end

  pos_x = 0
  pos_y = 12 * num
  (0..11).each do |i|
    (0..11).each do |j|
      piet_painting[pos_x + i, pos_y + j] = block[i, j]
    end
  end
end

def draw_end(num)
  block = ChunkyPNG::Image.new(12, 5, ChunkyPNG::Color::WHITE)

  old_push_color = current_color.push_color
  block[0, 0] = ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(*old_push_color)
  block[0, 1] = ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(*current_color.write_color)

  (0..2).each do |i|
    block[i, 3] = 0
  end

  block[1, 1] = 0
  block[2, 0] = 0
  block[2, 4] = 0

  (3..4).each do |j|
    block[3, j] = 0
  end

  (1..3).each do |j|
    block[2, j] = ChunkyPNG::Color.rgb(*current_color.write_color)
  end

  pos_x = 0
  pos_y = 12 * num
  (0..11).each do |i|
    (0..4).each do |j|
      piet_painting[pos_x + i, pos_y + j] = block[i, j]
    end
  end
end

require 'chunky_png'

class PietCompiler
  CTABLE = [
    [192, 0, 0], [0, 192, 0], [0, 0, 192], [192, 192, 0], [192, 0, 192], [0, 192, 192],
    [255, 0, 0], [0, 255, 0], [0, 0, 255], [255, 255, 0], [255, 0, 255], [0, 255, 255]
  ]

  def initialize(img_path)
    @image = ChunkyPNG::Image.from_file(img_path)
  end

  def compile
    y = 0
    while y < @image.height
      x = 0
      while x < @image.width
        color = @image[x, y]
        x += process_color(x, y, color)
      end
      y += 1
    end
  end

  private

  def process_color(x, y, color)
    r, g, b = color_to_rgb(color)
    idx = find_color_index(r, g, b)

    if idx
      return analyze_transition(x, y, idx)
    else
      return 1
    end
  end

  def color_to_rgb(color)
    [
      ChunkyPNG::Color.r(color),
      ChunkyPNG::Color.g(color),
      ChunkyPNG::Color.b(color)
    ]
  end

  def find_color_index(r, g, b)
    CTABLE.index([r, g, b])
  end

  def analyze_transition(x, y, idx)
    next_color = x < @image.width - 1 ? @image[x + 1, y] : nil

    if next_color
      next_r, next_g, next_b = color_to_rgb(next_color)
      next_idx = find_color_index(next_r, next_g, next_b)

      if next_idx
        hue_diff = (next_idx % 6 - idx % 6 + 6) % 6
        lightness_diff = (next_idx / 6 - idx / 6 + 2) % 2

        # Implement your logic to convert hue_diff and lightness_diff into Piet commands.
        # For example:
        # case [hue_diff, lightness_diff]
        # when [1, 0]
        #   puts "pointer"
        # when [2, 0]
        #   puts "switch"
        # end
      end
    end

    # Return 1 to move to the next color in the row
    1
  end
end

POSE_GRAPH.constraint_builder.min_score = 0.55
POSE_GRAPH.constraint_builder.global_localization_min_score = 0.6

-- 提高回环检测频率 (例如每一个或几个子图)
POSE_GRAPH.constraint_builder.sampling_ratio = 0.03

-- 为执行回环整形最小距离阈值（距离较远时不能执行回环检测）
POSE_GRAPH.constraint_builder.loop_closure_translation_weight = 1e4
POSE_GRAPH.constraint_builder.loop_closure_rotation_weight = 1e5

-- 调整fast_correlative_scan_matcher 参数(根据传感器和环境调整)
POSE_GRAPH.matcher_translation_weight = 5e2
POSE_GRAPH.matcher_rotation_weight = 1.6e3
POSE_GRAPH.matcher.ceres_scan_matcher_3d(optimizer_iterations=10, translation_weight=5.0, rotation_weight=3.0)
POSE_GRAPH.matcher.fast_correlative_scan_matcher.linear_search_window = 3
POSE_GRAPH.matcher.fast_correlative_scan_matcher.angular_search_window = math.rad(10.)
POSE_GRAPH.matcher.fast_correlative_scan_matcher_3d.min_rotational_score = 0.77
POSE_GRAPH.matcher.fast_correlative_scan_matcher_3d.min_low_resolution_score = 0.55

module ad9957_control(
  input clk,
  input rst,
  input [31:0] frequency,
  input [13:0] amplitude,
  output io_update,
  output reset,
  output [7:0] spi_data,
  output spi_clk,
  output spi_cs
);

parameter R0 = 8'b00000000; // 寄存器0地址
parameter R1 = 8'b00000001; // 寄存器1地址
parameter R2 = 8'b00000010; // 寄存器2地址
parameter R3 = 8'b00000011; // 寄存器3地址

reg [31:0] ftw_reg; // frequency tuning word
reg [13:0] ampl_reg; // amplitude tuning word
reg [7:0] spi_tx_buf; // SPI传输的数据缓存
reg [7:0] spi_rx_buf; // SPI接收的数据缓存
reg [2:0] spi_state; // SPI传输的状态机

assign io_update = spi_state == 3; // SPI传输完成，更新寄存器
assign reset = rst; // 外部复位信号

// SPI传输状态机，具体过程需要根据AD9957的时序图来确定
always @ (posedge clk) begin
  case (spi_state)
    0: begin // 待机状态，等待更新寄存器
      spi_tx_buf <= 8'b00000000;
      spi_state <= io_update ? 1 : 0;
    end
    1: begin // 发送寄存器地址
      spi_tx_buf <= {3'b000, spi_data[7:3]};
      spi_state <= 2;
    end
    2: begin // 发送寄存器数据
      spi_tx_buf <= spi_data[2:0] == 3'b011 ? 8'hff : 8'b00000000; // 读寄存器需要发送一个虚拟数据
      spi_state <= spi_data[2:0] == 3'b011 ? 0 : 3; // 如果是读寄存器，直接进入待机状态
    end
    3: begin // 传输完成，更新寄存器
      spi_rx_buf <= spi_data[2:0] == 3'b011 ? spi_rx_buf : 8'b00000000; // 如果是写寄存器，清除接收缓存
      spi_state <= 0;
    end
  endcase
end

// 时钟分频计数器，用于产生AD9957的系统时钟
reg [21:0] clk_cnt;
localparam FREQ_DIV = 22'd99999; // 50MHz / (FREQ_DIV + 1) = 500Hz
wire sys_clk = clk_cnt == FREQ_DIV;

always @ (posedge clk) begin
  if (rst) begin // 外部复位
    spi_state <= 0;
    ftw_reg <= 0;
    ampl_reg <= 0;
    spi_tx_buf <= 0;
    spi_rx_buf <= 0;
    spi_clk <= 0;
    spi_cs <= 1;
  end else begin
    clk_cnt <= sys_clk ? 0 : clk_cnt + 1; // 时钟分频计数器

    // 控制AD9957输出正弦波
    if (sys_clk) begin
      spi_data <= R0; // 选择寄存器0
      ftw_reg <= frequency * ((1 << 32) / 500000000); // 计算频率调谐字
      spi_data <= {16'd16384, ftw_reg[31:16], ftw_reg[15:0]}; // 设置频率调谐字
      spi_cs <= 0; // 载入频率调谐字
    end else if (spi_state == 3) begin
      // 频率调谐字载入完成，设置振幅和其它参数
      spi_data <= R1; // 选择寄存器1
      ampl_reg <= amplitude * (1 << 14) / 4095; // 计算振幅调谐字
      spi_data <= {14'b00000000000000, ampl_reg[13:8]}; // 设置振幅调谐字的高字节
      spi_cs <= 0; // 载入振幅调谐字的高字节
    end else if (spi_state == 3) begin
      spi_data <= {14'b00000000, ampl_reg[7:0]}; // 设置振幅调谐字的低字节
      spi_cs <= 0; // 载入振幅调谐字的低字节
    end else if (spi_state == 3) begin
      spi_data <= R2; // 选择寄存器2
      spi_data <= 8'b00000100; // 使能M（mixer）模块
      spi_cs <= 0;
    end else if (spi_state == 3) begin
      spi_data <= R3; // 选择寄存器3
      spi_data <= 8'b00001000; // 使能DAC输出
      spi_cs <= 0;
    end else begin
      spi_data <= 8'b00000000; // 等待下一个时钟周期
      spi_cs <= 1; // 结束传输
    end

    spi_clk <= spi_state == 2; // SPI传输时钟
  end
end

endmodule

//@version=4
strategy("ICT Enhanced Concepts Strategy", overlay=true, pyramiding=0)

// Inputs
lookbackPeriod = input(20, title="Lookback period for fractals", minval=1)
riskPercent = input(1.0, title="Risk Percent")
fibRetracementLevel = input(62, title="Fibonacci Retracement Level") * 0.01
atrLength = input(14, title="ATR Length")

// Calculate fractals and structure
leftFractal = (highest(high, lookbackPeriod) > highest(high, lookbackPeriod-1)[1]) and (highest(high, lookbackPeriod) > highest(high, lookbackPeriod+1)[2])
rightFractal = (lowest(low, lookbackPeriod) < lowest(low, lookbackPeriod-1)[1]) and (lowest(low, lookbackPeriod) < lowest(low, lookbackPeriod+1)[2])

highFractal = line.new(na, na, na, na, width=2, color=color.red)
line.delete(highFractal[1]) when leftFractal
line.set_xy1(highFractal, bar_index[lookbackPeriod], high)
line.set_xy2(highFractal, bar_index, high)

lowFractal = line.new(na, na, na, na, width=2, color=color.green)
line.delete(lowFractal[1]) when rightFractal
line.set_xy1(lowFractal, bar_index[lookbackPeriod], low)
line.set_xy2(lowFractal, bar_index, low)

// Calculate risk
atr = atr(atrLength)
risk = atr * riskPercent

// Calculate Optimal Trade Entry
longOTE = low + (high - low) * (1 - fibRetracementLevel)
shortOTE = high - (high - low) * fibRetracementLevel

// Market Structure Shift
bullishCandle = close > open
bearishCandle = close < open
candleHeightBull = bullishCandle ? close - open : na
candleHeightBear = bearishCandle ? open - close : na
candleHeightBars = max(lookbackPeriod, barsince(cross(close, shortOTE)))
averageCandleHeight = sma(bullishCandle ? candleHeightBull : candleHeightBear, candleHeightBars)
bullishMarketShift = (candleHeightBull != na and candleHeightBull > averageCandleHeight) or (candleHeightBear != na and candleHeightBear > averageCandleHeight)
bearishMarketShift = (candleHeightBear != na and candleHeightBear > averageCandleHeight) or (candleHeightBull != na and candleHeightBull > averageCandleHeight)

// Liquidity Displacement
liquidityDisplacement = low < lowest(low, lookbackPeriod)[1] and high > highest(high, lookbackPeriod)[1]

// Execution Conditions
enterLong = crossover(close, longOTE) and bullishMarketShift and liquidityDisplacement
enterShort = crossunder(close, shortOTE) and bearishMarketShift and liquidityDisplacement

stopLossLong = low - atr
stopLossShort = high + atr
exitLong = open > low and open < high and cross(close, stopLossLong)
exitShort = open < high and open > low and cross(close, stopLossShort)

// Execute trades
strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long, when=enterLong)
strategy.entry("Short", strategy.short, when=enterShort)

strategy.close("Long", when=exitLong)
strategy.close("Short", when=exitShort)

// Inducements
longsOnly = input(false, title="Show Long Inducements Only")
shortsOnly = input(false, title="Show Short Inducements Only")

plot(enterLong and not shortsOnly ? longOTE : na, style=plot.style_cross, color=color.green, linewidth=2, title="Long Entry")
plot(enterShort and not longsOnly ? shortOTE : na, style=plot.style_cross, color=color.red, linewidth=2, title="Short Entry")
plot(atr, title="ATR", color=color.blue)

surface.reverse! if surface.normal.z < 0
lines.each { |line| surface.followme(line) }

# Displace the surface vertices
surface.vertices.each { |vertex|
  vertex.position.z += disp_height.to_f
}

# Tesselate the surface for a smoother appearance
surface.erase!
surface = Sketchup.active_model.entities.add_face(lines.map(&:start).uniq)
surface.reverse! if surface.normal.z < 0
lines.each { |line| surface.followme(line) }
surface.vertices.each(&:smooth!)

# Hide the original lines
lines.each(&:hidden=)

# Refresh the view
Sketchup.active_model.active_view.refresh

// Set the number of bars to look back

level4 = lowest + (diff * 1)

# Open the binary file in read and write mode
File.open('filename.bin', 'rb+') do |file|
  # Read the whole file content
  content = file.read

  # Replace the hex values with zeros
 content.gsub!(/\x57\x72\x61\x70\x54\x61\x72\x67\x65\x74/, "\x00" * 10)

  # Write back the modified content to the file
  file.seek(0)
  file.write(content)
end

defmodule ListReverse do
  def reverse(list), do: reverse(list, [])

  defp reverse([], acc), do: acc
  defp reverse([head | tail], acc), do: reverse(tail, [head | acc])
end

dayofyear(_time) =>
    _year = year(_time)
    leapYear = (_year % 400 == 0) or (_year % 4 == 0 and _year % 100 != 0)
    dayCount = array.from(31, leapYear ? 29 : 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31)
    timeMonth = month(_time)
    dayofyear = 0
    if timeMonth > 1
        for i = 0 to timeMonth - 2
            dayofyear += dayCount.get(i)
    dayofyear + dayofmonth(_time)

getUNIXTimeFromJD(julianDay) =>
    z = math.floor(julianDay + 0.5)
    f = (julianDay + 0.5) % 1
    alpha = math.floor((z - 1867216.25) / 36524.25)
    a = (z < 2299161) ? z : (z + 1 + alpha - math.floor(alpha / 4.0))
    b = a + 1524
    c = math.floor((b - 122.1) / 365.25)
    d = math.floor(365.25 *)
    e = math.floor((b - d) / 30.6001)
    dayFloat = b - d - math.floor(30.6001 * e) + f
    _day = int(dayFloat)
    _month = (e < 13.5) ? int(e - 1) : int(e - 13)
    _year = (_month > 2.5) ? int(c - 4716) : int(c - 4715)
    secondTotal = int((dayFloat % 1) * 60 * 60 * 24)
    _hour = secondTotal / (60 * 60)
    _minute = (secondTotal - (_hour * 60 * 60)) / 60
    _second = secondTotal % 60
    timestamp(_year, _month, _day, _hour, _minute, _second)

getLastNewMoon(_time) =>
    _year = year(_time)
    dayOfYear = dayofyear(_time)
    k = (dayOfYear / 364.25 + _year - 1900) * 12.3685
    int moonPhase = na

    // 0 is equal to the fractional part of the new moon
    // 0.25 - first quarter, 0.5 - full moon, 0.75 - third quarter
    if ((k % 1.0) < 0.5)
        k := math.floor(k)
        moonPhase := +1
    else
        k := math.floor(k) + 0.5
        moonPhase := -1

    t = k / 1236.85
    
    // mean anomaly of the sun at the time julianDate
    anomalySun = math.toradians(359.2242 + (29.10535608 * k) - (0.0000333 * math.pow(t, 2)) - (0.00000347 * math.pow(t, 3)))
    // mean anomaly of the moon at the time julianDate
    anomalyMoon = math.toradians(306.0253 + (385.81691806 * k) + (0.0107306 * math.pow(t, 2)) + (0.00001236 * math.pow(t, 3)))
    // argument of latitude of the moon
    f = math.toradians(21.2964 + ((390.67050646 * k) - (0.0016528 * math.pow(t, 2)) - (0.00000239 * math.pow(t, 3))))
    dev = (0.1734 - (0.000393 * t)) * math.sin(anomalySun)
          + 0.0021 * math.sin(2 * anomalySun)
          - 0.4068 * math.sin(anomalyMoon)
          + 0.0161 * math.sin(2 * anomalyMoon)
          - 0.0004 * math.sin(3 * anomalyMoon)
          + 0.0104 * math.sin(2 * f)
          - 0.0051 * math.sin(anomalySun + anomalyMoon)
          - 0.0074 * math.sin(anomalySun - anomalyMoon)
          + 0.0004 * math.sin(2 * f + anomalySun)
          - 0.0004 * math.sin(2 * f - anomalySun)
          - 0.0006 * math.sin(2 * f + anomalyMoon)
          + 0.0010 * math.sin(2 * f - anomalyMoon)
          + 0.0005 * math.sin(anomalySun + 2 * anomalyMoon)

    julianDate = 2415020.75933 + (29.53058868 * k) + (0.0001178 * math.pow(t, 2)) - (0.000000155 * math.pow(t, 3)) +
          (0.00033 * math.sin(math.toradians(166.56) + (math.toradians(132.87) * t) - (math.toradians(0.009173) * math.pow(t, 2)))) + dev
    timeLastMoonPhase = getUNIXTimeFromJD(julianDate)
    timeLastMoonPhase := timeLastMoonPhase >= _time ? timeLastMoonPhase[1] : timeLastMoonPhase

    var int moonPhaseAdjusted = moonPhase
    moonPhaseAdjusted := barstate.isfirst or ta.change(timeLastMoonPhase) ? moonPhase : moonPhaseAdjusted[1]
    moonType = ta.change(moonPhaseAdjusted) ? moonPhase : na
    [moonPhaseAdjusted, moonType]

require 'gosu'

class GameWindow < Gosu::Window
  def initialize
    super(800, 600)  # Set the window dimensions

    self.caption = '3D Illusion and Circle Animation'  # Set the window title

    @rectangle_position = 100  # Initial position of the rectangle
    @circle1_x = 200  # Initial x-position of the first circle
    @circle2_x = 600  # Initial x-position of the second circle
    @circle_color = Gosu::Color::WHITE  # Initial color of the circles
  end

  def update
    @rectangle_position += 2  # Move the rectangle position by 2 pixels on each update

    @circle1_x += 1  # Move the first circle to the right
    @circle2_x -= 1  # Move the second circle to the left

    merge_distance = (@circle2_x - @circle1_x).abs  # Calculate the distance between the circles
    if merge_distance <= 50  # If circles are close enough, change their color gradually to green
      @circle_color.red -= 1  # Decrease the red component of the color
      @circle_color.green += 1  # Increase the green component of the color
    end
  end

  def draw
    # Clear the screen
    Gosu.draw_rect(0, 0, 800, 600, Gosu::Color::BLACK)

    # Draw the animated rectangle with a 3D illusion effect
    draw_3d_rectangle(@rectangle_position)

    # Draw and animate the circles
    draw_circle(@circle1_x, 300, 50, @circle_color)
    draw_circle(@circle2_x, 300, 50, @circle_color)
  end

  def draw_3d_rectangle(x)
    # Draw a 3D rectangle illusion effect
    Gosu.draw_rect(x, 200, 200, 200, Gosu::Color::RED, 1)
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 10, 210, 180, 180, Gosu::Color::RED, 0)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 20, 220, 160, 160, Gosu::Color::RED, 1)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 30, 230, 140, 140, Gosu::Color::RED, 0)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 40, 240, 120, 120, Gosu::Color::RED, 1)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 50, 250, 100, 100, Gosu::Color::RED, 0)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 60, 260, 80, 80, Gosu::Color::RED, 1)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 70, 270, 60, 60, Gosu::Color::RED, 0)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 80, 280, 40, 40, Gosu::Color::RED, 1)  
    Gosu.draw_rect(x + 90, 290, 20, 20, Gosu::Color::RED, 0)  
  end

  def draw_circle(x, y, radius, color)
    # Draw a circle at the specified position with the provided radius and color
    segments = 36  # Number of line segments used to draw the circle
    angle = 0  # Initialize the starting angle
    increment = 2 * Math::PI / segments  # Calculate the angle increment

    segments.times do |i|
      x1 = x + radius * Math.cos(angle + i * increment)
      y1 = y + radius * Math.sin(angle + i * increment)
      x2 = x + radius * Math.cos(angle + (i + 1) * increment)
      y2 = y + radius * Math.sin(angle + (i + 1) * increment)
      Gosu.draw_line(x1, y1, color, x2, y2, color)  # Draw line segment
    end
  end
end

require 'gosu'

class GameWindow < Gosu::Window
  def initialize
    super(800, 600)
    self.caption = "Text Spiral Animation"
    
    @angle = 0
    @radius = 50
    @font = Gosu::Font.new(24)
  end

  def update
    @angle += 1
    @radius += 1
  end

  def draw
    x = (Math.cos(@angle * Math::PI / 180) * @radius + 400).to_i
    y = (Math.sin(@angle * Math::PI / 180) * @radius + 300).to_i
    
    @font.draw_text('Hello, World!', x, y, 1)
  end
end

def generate_token(username)
  token = ""
  username.each_byte { |char| token += char.to_s }
  token += rand(1000..9999).to_s
  token
end

def main()
  print "Enter the bot's username: "
  username = gets.chomp
  token = generate_token(username)
  puts "Token: #{token}"
  sleep 10  # Keeps the program running for 10 seconds before closing
end

class Room
  attr_accessor :name, :description, :exits, :items

  def initialize(name, description, exits, items = [])
    @name = name
    @description = description
    @exits = exits
    @items = items
  end
end

class Game
  def initialize
    @rooms = []
    @current_room = nil
    @inventory = []
  end

  def add_room(room)
    @rooms << room
  end

  def start(room_name)
    @current_room = @rooms.find { |room| room.name == room_name }
    play_game
  end

  def play_game
    loop do
      puts "-------------------------------------------------"
      puts @current_room.description
      puts "You can go: #{list_exits}"
      puts "You have: #{list_inventory}"
      print "Command: "
      command = gets.strip.downcase

      case command
      when "quit", "exit"
        puts "Goodbye!"
        break
      when "inventory", "inv"
        puts "You have: #{list_inventory}"
      when "look"
        puts @current_room.description
        puts "You see: #{list_items}"
      else
        navigate(command)
      end
    end
  end

  def navigate(direction)
    exit = @current_room.exits[direction]
    if exit.nil?
      puts "You can't go that way. Try another direction."
    else
      @current_room = @rooms.find { |room| room.name == exit }
    end
  end

  def list_exits
    @current_room.exits.keys.join(", ")
  end

  def list_items
    @current_room.items.join(", ")
  end

  def list_inventory
    (@inventory.empty? ? "nothing" : @inventory.join(", "))
  end
end

                             0,  # 序号
                             0,  # 确认号

                        total_length,  # 总长度（根据TCP头部和数据长度计算）
                        0,  # 标识
                        0,  # 标志位和片偏移
                        255,  # 生存时间
                        socket.IPPROTO_TCP,  # 协议（TCP）
                        0,  # 校验和（根据IP头部和数据计算）

          (chord :f, :major),

          (chord :a, :minor)]

# Define the rhythm
rhythm = [0.5, 0.5, 1, 1]
# (change the rhythm array length as per the number of chords)

# Play the melody
live_loop :piano_melody do
  index = tick % chords.length
  
  # Play the chord
  play_chord chords[index], sustain: rhythm[index]
  
  # Play the individual notes in the chord
  chords[index].each do |note|
    play note - 12, release: rhythm[index] # shift the notes down an octave
    sleep rhythm[index]
  end
end

        value: request.referrer,
        expires: 1.week.from_now
      }
    end
  end
end

elseif rep.rate_options == "Allow multirate processing"
    buffer_matrix = zeros(size(input_signal, 1) * rep.repetition_count, size(input_signal, 2))
    for i in 1:rep.repetition_count
        start_index = (i - 1) * size(input_signal, 1) + 1
        end_index = start_index + size(input_signal, 1) - 1
        buffer_matrix[start_index:end_index, :] = input_signal
    end
    buffer_lines = size(buffer_matrix, 1)
    num_splits = div(buffer_lines, rep.repetition_count)
    output_signal = [buffer_matrix[(i-1)*buffer_lines+1:i*buffer_lines, :] for i in 1:num_splits]
    return output_signal
end

elseif rep.rate_options == "Allow multirate processing"
    rows, cols = size(input_signal)
    new_rows = rows * rep.repetition_count
    buffer_matrix = zeros(new_rows, cols) * 1.0
    for i in 1:rows
        for j in 1:rep.repetition_count
            buffer_matrix[(i-1)*rep.repetition_count+j, :] = input_signal[i, :]
        end
    end
    
    num_rows, num_cols = size(buffer_matrix)
    sub_matrices = Matrix{eltype(input_signal)}[]
    num_sub_matrices = ceil(Int, num_rows / rep.repetition_count)
    
    for i in 1:num_sub_matrices
        start_index = (i - 1) *  rep.repetition_count + 1
        end_index = min(i *  rep.repetition_count, num_rows)
        sub_matrix = buffer_matrix[start_index:end_index, :]
        push!(sub_matrices, sub_matrix)
    end
    
    # Adjust the size of the sub_matrices to match the size of input_signal
    sub_matrices_resized = []
    for sub_matrix in sub_matrices
        num_rows_sub, num_cols_sub = size(sub_matrix)
        if num_rows_sub > rows
            sub_matrix = sub_matrix[1:rows, :]
        elseif num_rows_sub < rows
            sub_matrix = vcat(sub_matrix, sub_matrix[num_rows_sub:end, :])
        end
        push!(sub_matrices_resized, sub_matrix)
    end
    
    return sub_matrices_resized
end

require 'minitest/autorun'

class AxisTiltTest < Minitest::Test
  def test_axis_tilt_daylength_effect
    1000.times do
      axis_tilt = -90 + rand(180)
      day_of_year = rand(365)

      result = axis_tilt_daylength_effect(axis_tilt, day_of_year)

      assert_instance_of(Float, result)
      assert_includes(0..2, result)

      if axis_tilt >= -90 && axis_tilt <= 90
        # Checking constraints for North/South Pole
        if day_of_year >= 81 && day_of_year <= 264
          # Polar day: length > 23h
          assert_operator(result, :>, 23)
        elsif day_of_year >= 273 || day_of_year <= 80
          # Polar night: length < 1h
          assert_operator(result, :<, 1)
        end
      else
        # Checking constraints for Equator
        assert_in_delta(result, 0, 0.083)
      end
    end
  end
end

def test_axis_tilt_daylength_effect
  # Polar night, length < 1 h
  # - North Pole: start 24. Sep, end on 22. Dec, Winter Solstice.
  # - South Pole: start 22. Mar, end 20. Jun, Summer Solstice of N. hemisphere.
  # Polar day, length > 23 h
  # - North Pole 21.3 - 23.9
  # - South 21.9 - 21.3.
  # Equatorial day varies < 5 minutes
  
  constraints = {
    polar_night: {
      north_pole: { start: 268, end: 356 }, # September 24 - December 22
      south_pole: { start: 80, end: 170 } # March 22 - June 20
    },
    polar_day: {
      north_pole: { start: 81, end: 264 }, # March 21 - September 20
      south_pole: { start: 81, end: 264 } # March 21 - September 20
    },
    equatorial_day: {
      start: 0, end: 364, variation: 0.083 # Full year with variation < 5 minutes
    }
  }

  1000.times do
    axis_tilt = -90 + rand(180)
    day_of_year = rand(365)

    result = axis_tilt_daylength_effect(axis_tilt, day_of_year)

    assert_instance_of(Float, result)
    assert_includes(0..2, result)

    if axis_tilt >= -90 && axis_tilt <= 90
      # Checking constraints for North/South Pole
      if day_of_year >= constraints[:polar_night][:north_pole][:start] && day_of_year <= constraints[:polar_night][:north_pole][:end]
        # Polar night: length < 1h
        assert_operator(result, :<, 1)
      elsif day_of_year >= constraints[:polar_day][:north_pole][:start] && day_of_year <= constraints[:polar_day][:north_pole][:end]
        # Polar day: length > 23h
        assert_operator(result, :>, 23)
      end
    else
      # Checking constraints for Equator
      assert_in_delta(result, 0, constraints[:equatorial_day][:variation])
    end
  end
end

wheelDirection = Vector2(-result.normal.y, result.normal.x)
wheelContactPoint = result.position - result.normal * wheelRadius
wheelForwardVelocity = wheelDirection.dot(result.collider.linear_velocity)
wheelSidewaysVelocity = -wheelDirection.cross(result.collider.linear_velocity)

wheelForwardForce = -wheelForwardVelocity * wheelFriction
wheelSidewaysForce = -wheelSidewaysVelocity * wheelFriction

result.collider.apply_impulse(wheelContactPoint, wheelDirection * (suspensionForce + wheelForwardForce))

  gather_facts: no

  tasks:
    - name: Get the contents of /etc/passwd
      ansible.builtin.shell: cat /etc/passwd
      register: passwd_output
      # You can also use the command module if you don't need shell features:
      # ansible.builtin.command: cat /etc/passwd

    - name: Save output to a file
      ansible.builtin.copy:
        dest: "/tmp/{{ inventory_hostname }}_etc_passwd.txt"
        content: "{{ passwd_output.stdout }}"
      delegate_to: localhost
      run_once: true

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      # Get schedules with the desired departure station
      departure_schedules = Schedule.joins(stations: :schedule)
                                    .where(stations: { name: departure_station })
      # Get schedules with the desired destination station
      destination_schedules = Schedule.joins(stations: :schedule)
                                      .where(stations: { name: destination_station })

      # Find trips where the departure station occurs before the destination station
      valid_trips = departure_schedules.where('stations.arrival_time < ?', destination_schedules.select('stations.arrival_time'))
                                       .pluck(:trip)

      # Select schedules that are part of valid trips and order them by the arrival time
      schedules = Schedule.where(trip: valid_trips)
                          .joins(:stations)
                          .distinct
                          .order('MIN(stations.arrival_time)')

      # Construct the response
      render json: schedules.map { |schedule|
        {
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: schedule.stations.order(:arrival_time).map { |station|
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time,
              departureTime: station.departure_time
            }
          }
        }
      }, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Schedule < ApplicationRecord
  has_many :stations
  
  scope :with_station, ->(station_name) { 
    joins(:stations).where(stations: { name: station_name }) 
  }

  scope :starting_after, ->(time) { 
    where('stations.arrival_time > ?', time)
  }
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      # Find all schedules that include the departure station
      departure_schedules = Schedule.with_station(departure_station)
      
      valid_schedules = []

      departure_schedules.each do |departure_schedule|
        # For each departure schedule, find if there is a corresponding schedule 
        # that includes the destination station, starting after the departure
        destination_schedules = Schedule.with_station(destination_station)
                                        .starting_after(departure_schedule.stations.find_by(name: departure_station).arrival_time)
                                        .where(trip: departure_schedule.trip)
        
        # Add to valid schedules if there's a match
        valid_schedules.concat(destination_schedules) if destination_schedules.present?
      end

      # Deduping by trip ID, to make sure each valid trip is represented once
      valid_schedules.uniq! { |schedule| schedule.trip }

      # Construct the response
      render json: valid_schedules.map { |schedule|
        {
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: schedule.stations.order(:arrival_time).map { |station|
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
              departureTime: station.departure_time.strftime('%I:%M %p')
            }
          }
        }
      }, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      schedules = Schedule.joins(:stations)
                          .where(stations: { name: departure_station })
                          .where(Schedule.arel_table[:id].in(
                            Schedule.joins(:stations)
                            .where(stations: { name: destination_station})
                            .where('stations.arrival_time > stations_departures.arrival_time')
                            .where('stations.schedule_id = stations_departures.schedule_id')
                            .select(:id)
                          ))
                          .select('schedules.*, stations.arrival_time AS departure_arrival_time')
                          .from('schedules, stations as stations_departures')
                          .where('schedules.id = stations_departures.schedule_id')
                          .where('stations_departures.name': departure_station)
                          .distinct
                          .order('departure_arrival_time')
      
      render json: schedules.map { |schedule|
        {
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: schedule.stations.order(:arrival_time).map { |station|
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
              departureTime: station.departure_time.strftime('%I:%M %p')
            }
          }.reject { |s| s[:arrivalTime] < schedule.departure_arrival_time }  # Filters out stations occurring before the departure station
        }
      }, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      # Find the IDs of schedules containing the destination station.
      destination_schedule_ids = Station.where(name: destination_station).select(:schedule_id)

      schedules = Schedule.joins(:stations)
                          .where(stations: { name: departure_station, schedule_id: destination_schedule_ids })
                          .select('schedules.*, stations.arrival_time AS departure_arrival_time')
                          .distinct
                          .order('departure_arrival_time')

      # Map the schedules to JSON, including filtering for stations after the departure station.
      render json: schedules.map { |schedule|
        stations = schedule.stations
                           .where('arrival_time > ?', schedule.departure_arrival_time)
                           .order(:arrival_time)
                           .map { |station|
                             {
                               station: station.name,
                               arrivalTime: station.arrival_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
                               departureTime: station.departure_time.strftime('%I:%M %p')
                             }
                           }
        
        next if stations.blank? # Skip schedules with no valid stations after the departure station.
        
        {
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: stations
        }
      }.compact, status: :ok # Use compact to remove any nil values from the map.
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      # Pre-load the stations with a sequence number greater than the departure station
      schedules = Schedule.includes(:stations).where(stations: { name: departure_station }).order('stations.sequence_number')
      
      render json: schedules.map { |schedule|
        departure_station_index = schedule.stations.index { |station| station.name == departure_station }
        {
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: schedule.stations[departure_station_index+1..-1].map { |station| # Only stations after the departure station
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
              departureTime: station.departure_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
              sequenceNumber: station.sequence_number
            }
          }.select { |station| station[:station] == destination_station || station[:sequenceNumber] > departure_station_index } # Filters out stations before the destination station
        }
      }, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      # Find the departure and destination stations and their respective schedules based on the station names
      departure_schedules = Station.joins(:schedule).where(name: departure_station)
      destination_schedules = Station.joins(:schedule).where(name: destination_station)

      # Select Schedules where the destination station comes after the departure station within the same route
      valid_schedule_ids = (departure_schedules & destination_schedules).map(&:schedule_id).uniq
      schedules = Schedule.includes(:stations).where(id: valid_schedule_ids)

      render json: schedules.map { |schedule|
        {
          trip: schedule.route.bus_schedule.id,
          stations: schedule.stations.order(:id).map { |station|
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
              departureTime: station.departure_time.strftime('%I:%M %p')
            }
          }.drop_while { |s| s[:station] != departure_station } # Starts with the departure station
           .drop(1) # Excludes the departure station itself
           .take_while { |s| s[:station] != destination_station } # Continues until (but doesn't include) the destination station
        }
      }, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      schedules = Schedule.includes(:stations)  # Include related stations to reduce DB queries
                          .select { |schedule| 
                            schedule_has_correct_itinerary(schedule, departure_station, destination_station)
                          }

      render json: schedules.map { |schedule|
        {
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: schedule.stations.select { |station| 
            included_in_itinerary?(station, schedule, departure_station, destination_station) 
          }.map { |station|
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
              departureTime: station.departure_time.strftime('%I:%M %p')
            }
          }
        }
      }, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end

  private

  def schedule_has_correct_itinerary(schedule, departure_station, destination_station)
    departure_index = station_index(schedule.stations, departure_station)
    destination_index = station_index(schedule.stations, destination_station)

    departure_index && destination_index && departure_index < destination_index
  end

  def included_in_itinerary?(station, schedule, departure_station, destination_station)
    departure_index = station_index(schedule.stations, departure_station)
    destination_index = station_index(schedule.stations, destination_station)
    current_station_index = station_index(schedule.stations, station.name)

    current_station_index && departure_index && destination_index &&
      current_station_index > departure_index && current_station_index <= destination_index
  end

  def station_index(stations, station_name)
    stations.index { |station| station.name == station_name }
  end
end

      valid_schedules = departing_schedules.where(id: arriving_schedules.pluck(:id))

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      # Assuming 'stations' table has a 'position' field to order by.
      schedules = Schedule.joins(:stations, route: :bus_schedule)
                          .where(stations: { name: [departure_station, destination_station] })
                          .distinct
                          .includes(:stations, route: :bus_schedule)
                          .order('stations.position ASC')  # Add order to ensure correct sequence

      vehicle_trips = schedules.each_with_object({}) do |schedule, acc|
        # Use pluck to retrieve ordered names and ids to avoid N+1 query problems
        station_names_ids = schedule.stations.pluck(:name, :id)
        station_names = station_names_ids.map(&:first)
        station_ids = station_names_ids.map(&:last)

        # Ensure that the destination comes after the departure
        if station_names.include?(departure_station) &&
           station_names.include?(destination_station) &&
           station_names.index(departure_station) < station_names.index(destination_station)

          vehicle_number = schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number

          # Find indexes for departure and destination
          departure_index = station_names.index(departure_station)
          destination_index = station_names.index(destination_station)

          # Select all stations between, including departure and destination
          relevant_station_ids = station_ids[departure_index..destination_index]

          trip_data = {
            trip: schedule.trip,
            stations: schedule.stations.where(id: relevant_station_ids).map do |station|
              {
                station: station.name,
                arrivalTime: station.arrival_time,
                departureTime: station.departure_time
              }
            end
          }

          # Accumulate trips for each vehicle_number
          acc[vehicle_number] ||= []
          acc[vehicle_number] << trip_data
        end
      end

      render json: vehicle_trips.map { |vehicle_number, trips|
        {
          vehicle_number: vehicle_number,
          trips: trips
        }
      }, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]
    destination_station = params[:destination]

    if departure_station.blank? || destination_station.blank?
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
      return
    end

    # Fetch schedules that include both departure and destination stations
    schedules = Schedule.joins(:stations, route: :bus_schedule)
                        .where(stations: { name: [departure_station, destination_station] })
                        .distinct
                        .order('stations.position asc') # assuming there is a field `position` to define station order in a route
                        .includes(:stations, route: :bus_schedule)

    valid_schedules = []

    # Iterate through schedules to find the valid paths
    schedules.find_each do |schedule|
      # Get station names along with their positions to check the order
      station_data = schedule.stations.pluck(:name, :position)
      stations_hash = station_data.to_h

      if stations_hash[departure_station].present? && stations_hash[destination_station].present? &&
         stations_hash[departure_station] < stations_hash[destination_station]

        # Find intermediate stations based on their position
        intermediate_stations = schedule.stations.where(position: (stations_hash[departure_station] + 1)...stations_hash[destination_station])
                                                 .order(position: :asc)

        complete_stations = [schedule.stations.find_by(name: departure_station)] +
                            intermediate_stations +
                            [schedule.stations.find_by(name: destination_station)]

        trip_data = {
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: complete_stations.map do |station|
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time,
              departureTime: station.departure_time
            }
          end
        }

        vehicle_number = schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number
        valid_schedules.push({ vehicle_number: vehicle_number, trip_data: trip_data })
      end
    end

    # Group by vehicle number for the final output
    vehicle_trips = valid_schedules.group_by { |sch| sch[:vehicle_number] }
                                   .transform_values { |vals| vals.map { |val| val[:trip_data] } }

    # Render the final JSON response
    render json: vehicle_trips.map { |vehicle_number, trips|
      {
        vehicle_number: vehicle_number,
        trips: trips
      }
    }, status: :ok
  end
end

      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
      return
    end
    
    # Optimize by joining and eager loading required associations in a single query, and filtering directly in the database.
    schedules = Schedule
                  .joins(route: :bus_schedule, stations: :schedule)
                  .where(stations: { name: [departure_station, destination_station] })
                  .select('schedules.*, stations.*, bus_schedules.vehicle_number')
                  .order('stations.arrival_time ASC')
                  .distinct
    
    trips = schedules.each_with_object([]) do |schedule, trip_list|
      # Get stations only for the relevant schedule to avoid N+1 queries
      stations = schedule.stations.order('arrival_time ASC')
      departure_index = stations.find_index { |stat| stat.name == departure_station }
      destination_index = stations.find_index { |stat| stat.name == destination_station }

      next unless departure_index && destination_index && departure_index < destination_index

      trip_list << {
        vehicle_number: schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number,
        trip: schedule.trip,
        stations: stations.map { |station|
          {
            station: station.name,
            arrivalTime: station.arrival_time.strftime('%I:%M %p'),
            departureTime: station.departure_time.strftime('%I:%M %p')
          }
        }
      }
    end

    # Sort the trips by the departure time of the departure station
    sorted_trips = trips.sort_by { |trip| 
      trip[:stations].find { |station| station[:station] == departure_station }[:departureTime]
    }

defmodule StairsClimber do
  # 对外提供的公共函数，接收楼梯阶梯数n
  def climb_stairs(n) when n >= 0 do
    # 调用内部函数计算结果
    climb_stairs(n, Stream.iterate({1, 1}, fn {second_last, last} -> {last, second_last + last} |> elem(1) end))
  end

  # 私有辅助函数，遍历动态规划的惰性序列
  defp climb_stairs(0, _), do: 1
  defp climb_stairs(1, _), do: 1
  defp climb_stairs(n, stream) when n > 1 do
    # 跳过前n - 1个值，在Stream中获取第n个值
    stream |> Enum.drop(n - 1) |> Enum.at(0)
  end
end

module clock_synchronizer_8bit(
    input wire clk,                 // Clock input
    input wire async_reset,         // Asynchronous reset input, active high
    input wire [7:0] async_data_in, // Asynchronous data input
    output reg [7:0] sync_data_out  // Synchronized data output
);

reg [7:0] sync_stage1; // Intermediate synchronization stage

// Synchronous logic for two-stage synchronization
always @(posedge clk or posedge async_reset) begin
    if (async_reset) begin
        sync_stage1 <= 8'b0;      // Asynchronously reset the first stage
        sync_data_out <= 8'b0;    // Asynchronously reset the second stage/output
    end else begin
        sync_stage1 <= async_data_in; // First synchronization stage
        sync_data_out <= sync_stage1; // Second synchronization stage/output
    end
end

endmodule

require 'time'

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure].strip.upcase if params[:departure].present?
    destination_station = params[:destination].strip.upcase if params[:destination].present?
    
    time_param = params[:time]
    exclude_param = params[:restrict]
    time = time_param.present? ? Time.parse(time_param) : nil
    exclude = exclude_param.present? ? exclude_param.downcase == 'true' : false

    if departure_station.present? && destination_station.present?
      # Search stations that start with the provided string using the 'LIKE' operator.
      # This assumes you're using SQLite. For a case-insensitive search use 'ILIKE' if it's supported.
      schedules = Schedule.joins(:stations)
                          .where('UPPER(stations.name) LIKE ? OR UPPER(stations.name) LIKE ?', "#{departure_station}%", "#{destination_station}%")
                          .group('schedules.id')
                          .having('COUNT(DISTINCT stations.name) >= 2')
                          .distinct
                          .includes(:stations, route: :bus_schedule)

      trips = []
      schedules.each do |schedule|
        stations = schedule.stations.order(:id)
        station_names = stations.map { |station| station.name.upcase }

        # Use 'start_with?' method for searching the departure/destination.
        departure_index = station_names.index { |name| name.start_with?(departure_station) }
        destination_index = station_names.index { |name| name.start_with?(destination_station) }

        if departure_index && destination_index && departure_index < destination_index
          departure_station_data = stations[departure_index]
          departure_time = Time.parse(departure_station_data.departure_time)

          # Skip if time is given and departure is before that time
          next if time && departure_time < time

          trip_data = {
            vehicle_number: schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number,
            trip: schedule.trip,
            stations: stations.map do |station|
              {
                station: station.name,
                arrivalTime: station.arrival_time,
                departureTime: station.departure_time
              }
            end
          }

          # Exclude stations before departure and after destination if exclude parameter is true
          if exclude
            trip_data[:stations] = trip_data[:stations][departure_index..destination_index]
          end

          trips << trip_data
        end
      end

      # Sort trips by departure time
      sorted_trips = trips.sort_by do |trip|
        trip_data = trip[:stations].find { |station| station[:station].upcase.start_with?(departure_station) }
        Time.parse(trip_data[:departureTime])
      end
      render json: sorted_trips, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

require 'time'

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    if params[:departure].blank? || params[:destination].blank?
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
      return
    end

    departure_station = params[:departure].upcase
    destination_station = params[:destination].upcase
    time_param = params[:time]
    exclude_param = params[:restrict]
    desired_time = time_param.present? ? Time.parse(time_param) : nil
    exclude = exclude_param.present? && exclude_param.downcase == 'true'

    puts departure_station

    # Improved single SQL query
    schedules = Schedule.joins(stations: :route)
      .where('stations.name LIKE ? OR stations.name LIKE ?',
             "#{departure_station}%", "#{destination_station}%")
      .group('schedules.id')
      .having('COUNT(DISTINCT stations.name) >= 2')
      .preload(:stations, route: :bus_schedule)
      .to_a

    puts schedules

    trips = schedules.each_with_object([]) do |schedule, memo|
      stations = schedule.stations.sort_by(&:id)
      station_names = stations.map(&:name)

      departure_index = station_names.index { |name| name =~ /\A#{departure_station}/i }
      destination_index = station_names.index { |name| name =~ /\A#{destination_station}/i }

      next if departure_index.nil? || destination_index.nil? || departure_index >= destination_index
      
      departure_time = Time.parse(stations[departure_index].departure_time)
      next if desired_time && departure_time < desired_time

      trip_data = {
        vehicle_number: schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number,
        trip: schedule.trip,
        stations: stations[departure_index..destination_index].map do |station|
          {
            station: station.name,
            arrivalTime: station.arrival_time,
            departureTime: station.departure_time
          }
        end
      }

      memo << trip_data
    end

    # Sort by departure time
    sorted_trips = trips.sort_by do |trip|
      Time.parse(trip[:stations].first[:departureTime])
    end

    render json: sorted_trips, status: :ok
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]&.upcase.gsub('_', ' ')
    destination_station = params[:destination]&.upcase.gsub('_', ' ')
    time = params[:time].present? ? Time.parse(params[:time]) : nil
    exclude = params[:restrict]&.downcase == 'true'

    if departure_station && destination_station
      # Include the associated stations and bus schedules to avoid n+1 queries
      schedules = Schedule.includes(stations: { route: :bus_schedule })
                    .where('stations.name ILIKE ? OR stations.name ILIKE ?', "#{departure_station}%", "#{destination_station}%")
                    .references(:stations) # Necessary for where clauses on the included tables
                    .group('schedules.id')
                    .having('COUNT(DISTINCT stations.name) = 2')
                    .distinct 

      trips = []
      
      schedules.each do |schedule|
        stations = schedule.stations.order(:id)
        
        departure_index = stations.index { |station| station.name.match?(/^#{departure_station}/i) }
        destination_index = stations.index { |station| station.name.match?(/^#{destination_station}/i) }

        next if departure_index.nil? || destination_index.nil? || departure_index >= destination_index

        departure_time = Time.parse(stations[departure_index].departure_time)
        next if time && departure_time < time

        trip_data = build_trip_data(schedule, stations, departure_index, destination_index, exclude)
        trips << trip_data if trip_data
      end

      sorted_trips = trips.sort_by { |trip| Time.parse(trip[:stations].first[:departureTime]) }
      render json: sorted_trips, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end

  private

  def build_trip_data(schedule, stations, departure_index, destination_index, exclude)
    trip_stations = exclude ? stations[departure_index..destination_index] : stations
    {
      vehicle_number: schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number,
      trip: schedule.trip,
      stations: trip_stations.map do |station| 
        {
          station: station.name,
          arrivalTime: station.arrival_time,
          departureTime: station.departure_time
        }
      end
    }
  end
end

require 'time'

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    # Convert provided departure and destination station names to uppercase with spaces
    departure_station = params[:departure]&.upcase&.tr('_', ' ')
    destination_station = params[:destination]&.upcase&.tr('_', ' ')

    # Parse time if provided
    time = params[:time].present? ? Time.parse(params[:time]) : nil
    
    # Exclude return trips
    exclude_return = params[:restrict]&.downcase == 'true'

    # Check for the presence of required parameters
    if departure_station && destination_station
      stations = Station.select("s1.name departure_station, s2.name destination_station,
                                s1.schedule_id schedule_id, s1.departure_time departure_time, s2.arrival_time arrival_time")
                        .joins("JOIN stations s2 ON s1.schedule_id = s2.schedule_id")
                        .preload(schedule: { route: :bus_schedule })
                        .where("s1.name LIKE ? AND s2.name LIKE ?", "#{departure_station}%", "#{destination_station}%")

      trips = stations.map do |station|
        # Ensure stations are in correct order for a valid trip
        departure_time = Time.parse(station.departure_time)

        next if time && departure_time < time
        next if exclude_return && departure_time > Time.parse(station.arrival_time)

        {
          schedule_id: station.schedule_id,
          departure_station: station.departure_station,
          destination_station: station.destination_station,
          departure_time: station.departure_time,
          arrival_time: station.arrival_time,
          vehicle_number: station.schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number
        }
      end.compact

      # Sort trips by departure time
      sorted_trips = trips.sort_by { |trip| Time.parse(trip[:departure_time]) }

      render json: sorted_trips, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station = params[:departure]&.upcase
    destination_station = params[:destination]&.upcase

    time = params[:time].present? ? Time.parse(params[:time]) : nil
    exclude = params[:restrict]&.downcase == 'true'

    if departure_station && destination_station
      station_pairs = Station.select(
        "s1.name AS departure_station, s2.name AS destination_station, s1.schedule_id, s1.departure_time, s2.arrival_time"
      ).joins("INNER JOIN stations s2 ON s1.schedule_id = s2.schedule_id")
        .where("s1.name ILIKE ? AND s2.name ILIKE ?", "#{departure_station}%", "#{destination_station}%")

      trips = station_pairs.preload(schedule: { route: :bus_schedule }).map do |station_pair|
        next if time && Time.parse(station_pair.departure_time) < time

        schedule = station_pair.schedule
        trip_data = {
          vehicle_number: schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number,
          trip: schedule.trip,
          stations: schedule.stations.order(:id).map do |station|
            {
              station: station.name,
              arrivalTime: station.arrival_time,
              departureTime: station.departure_time
            }
          end
        }

        departure_index = trip_data[:stations].index { |s| s[:station].casecmp(departure_station).zero? }
        destination_index = trip_data[:stations].index { |s| s[:station].casecmp(destination_station).zero? }
        
        next unless departure_index && destination_index && departure_index < destination_index
        trip_data[:stations] = trip_data[:stations][departure_index...destination_index] if exclude
        trip_data
      end.compact

      sorted_trips = trips.sort_by { |trip| Time.parse(trip[:stations].first[:departureTime]) }
      
      render json: sorted_trips, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

class Api::V1::SchedulesController < ApplicationController
  def index
    departure_station_param = params[:departure]
    destination_station_param = params[:destination]

    if departure_station_param.present? && destination_station_param.present?
      departure_station = departure_station_param.upcase
      destination_station = destination_station_param.upcase

      time = params[:time].present? ? Time.parse(params[:time]) : nil
      exclude = params[:restrict]&.downcase == 'true'

      station_pairs = Station.select(
        "departure_stations.name AS departure_station_name, " +
        "destination_stations.name AS destination_station_name, " +
        "departure_stations.schedule_id, departure_stations.departure_time, " +
        "destination_stations.arrival_time"
      ).joins("INNER JOIN stations AS destination_stations " +
        "ON stations.schedule_id = destination_stations.schedule_id")
        .where("stations.name LIKE ? AND destination_stations.name LIKE ?", "#{departure_station}%", "#{destination_station}%")

      station_pairs = station_pairs.to_a.select do |station_pair|
        unless time.nil?
          departure_time = Time.parse(station_pair.departure_time)
          next if departure_time < time
        end

        true
      end

      trips_data = []
      station_pairs.each do |station_pair|
        schedule = Schedule.includes(route: :bus_schedule).find(station_pair.schedule_id)

        stations = schedule.stations.order(:id)
        departure_index = stations.index { |s| s.name.upcase.start_with?(departure_station) }
        destination_index = stations.index { |s| s.name.upcase.start_with?(destination_station) }

        if departure_index.present? && destination_index.present? && departure_index < destination_index
          if exclude
            stations = stations[departure_index..destination_index]
          end

          trips_data << {
            vehicle_number: schedule.route.bus_schedule.vehicle_number,
            trip: schedule.trip,
            stations: stations.map { |station| { station: station.name, arrivalTime: station.arrival_time, departureTime: station.departure_time } }
          }
        end
      end

      sorted_trips = trips_data.sort_by do |trip_data|
        Time.parse(trip_data[:stations].find { |station| station[:station].upcase.start_with?(departure_station) }[:departureTime])
      end

      render json: sorted_trips, status: :ok
    else
      render json: { error: 'Departure and destination stations are required.' }, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end
end

- name: Gather and Map Node Manager Port Mappings for Each Domain
  hosts: all
  gather_facts: no
  tasks:
    - name: Initialize nm_ports_per_domain if not defined
      set_fact:
        nm_ports_per_domain: {}
      when: nm_ports_per_domain is not defined

    - name: Gather Node Manager Port Mappings for Each Domain per Host
      set_fact:
        nm_ports_per_domain: >-
          {{
            nm_ports_per_domain | combine(
              { ansible_host: 
                { item.key: item.value.node_manager_port }
              }
            )
          }}
      loop: "{{ lookup('dict', hostvars[inventory_hostname]['domains']).items() }}"
      loop_control:
        loop_var: item
      vars:
        ansible_host: "{{ hostvars[inventory_hostname]['ansible_host'] }}"
      when: "'domains' in hostvars[inventory_hostname]"
      delegate_to: localhost
      run_once: true
      tags: [always]

    - name: Display nm_ports_per_domain

def bubble_sort(array)
  n = array.length
  loop do
    swapped = false

    (n-1).times do |i|
      if array[i] > array[i+1]
        array[i], array[i+1] = array[i+1], array[i]
        swapped = true
      end
    end

    break unless swapped
  end
  array
end

# Пример использования:
arr = [4, 3, 78, 2, 0, 2]
sorted_arr = bubble_sort(arr)
puts sorted_arr.inspect

def bubble_sort_optimized(array)
  n = array.length
  until n <= 1
    new_n = 0
    (1...n).each do |i|
      if array[i - 1] > array[i]
        array[i - 1], array[i] = array[i], array[i - 1]
        new_n = i
      end
    end
    n = new_n
  end
  array
end

# Пример использования:
arr = [4, 3, 78, 2, 0, 2]
sorted_arr = bubble_sort_optimized(arr)
puts sorted_arr.inspect

def quick_sort(array)
  return array if array.length <= 1

  pivot = array.delete_at(rand(array.length))
  left, right = array.partition { |element| element < pivot }

  quick_sort(left) + [pivot] + quick_sort(right)
end

# Пример использования:
arr = [34, 2, 1, 5, 3]
sorted_arr = quick_sort(arr)
puts sorted_arr.inspect

def merge_sort(array)
  if array.length <= 1
    return array
  else
    mid = array.length / 2
    left = merge_sort(array.slice(0, mid))
    right = merge_sort(array.slice(mid, array.length - mid))
    return merge(left, right)
  end
end

def merge(left, right)
  sorted_array = []
  until left.empty? || right.empty?
    if left.first <= right.first
      sorted_array << left.shift
    else
      sorted_array << right.shift
    end
  end
  sorted_array.concat(left).concat(right)
end

# Example usage:
arr = [4, 1, 5, 1, 33, 312]
sorted_arr = merge_sort(arr)
puts sorted_arr.inspect

expr
=> expr '$' expr       # Applying the second production rule (since we have the '$' operator in our string)
=> '(' expr ')' '$' expr  # Applying the fifth production rule to match the '('
=> '(' expr 'then' expr 'else' expr ')' '$' expr  # Applying the first production rule inside the parentheses
=> '(' INT 'then' expr 'else' expr ')' '$' expr  # Applying the sixth production rule to replace the first 'expr' with 'INT' (matching '1')
=> '(' INT 'then' '#' expr 'else' expr ')' '$' expr  # Applying the fourth production rule to match the '#' operator
=> '(' INT 'then' '#' INT 'else' expr ')' '$' expr  # Applying the sixth production again to replace 'expr' with 'INT' (matching '2')
=> '(' INT 'then' '#' INT 'else' INT ')' '$' expr  # Applying the sixth production again to replace the final 'expr' inside the 'then...else...' (matching '3')
=> '(' INT 'then' '#' INT 'else' INT ')' '$' INT  # Now, replacing the rightmost expr with INT (matching '4')

expr
=> expr ':' expr       # Using the third production rule
=> INT ':' expr        # Replacing the leftmost expr with INT (matching '1')
=> INT ':' expr '$' expr  # Using the second production rule
=> INT ':' INT '$' expr   # Replacing the leftmost expr with INT (matching '2')
=> INT ':' INT '$' INT   # Replacing the expr with INT (matching '3')

expr
=> expr '$' expr       # Using the second production rule
=> expr ':' expr '$' expr  # Using the third production rule on the leftmost expr
=> INT ':' expr '$' expr   # Replacing the leftmost expr with INT (matching '1')
=> INT ':' INT '$' expr   # Replacing the leftmost expr with INT (matching '2')
=> INT ':' INT '$' INT   # Replacing the expr with INT (matching '3')
